==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Filch
<hw>Filch</hw> <pr>(f⟦icr⟧lch)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Filched</conjf> <pr>(f⟦icr⟧lcht)</pr>; <pos>p. pr.
& vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Filching</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf. AS.
<ets>feolan</ets> to stick to, OHG. <ets>felhan</ets>,
<ets>felahan</ets>, to hide, Icel. <ets>fela</ets>, Goth.
<ets>filhan</ets> to hide, bury, Prov. E. <ets>feal</ets> to hide slyly,
OE. <ets>felen</ets>.]</ety> <def>To steal or take privily (commonly,
that which is of little value); to pilfer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Fain would they <qex>filch</qex> that little food away.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>But he that <qex>filches</qex> from me my good name,⟦br⟧
Robs me of that which not enriches him,⟦br⟧
And makes me poor indeed.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Filcher</ent>⟦br⟧
